### emitStoreWithImmOffset() {#a271310bf77ed9982cec75ffad22d2a98}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>void MipsTargetStreamer::emitStoreWithImmOffset (unsigned Opcode, unsigned SrcReg, unsigned BaseReg, int64&#95;t Offset, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/function-ref">function&#95;ref</a>&lt; unsigned()&gt; GetATReg, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smloc">SMLoc</a> IDLoc, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcsubtargetinfo">MCSubtargetInfo</a> &#42; STI)</>}>
Emit a store instruction with an offset.

Emit a store instruction with an immediate offset.

If the offset is out of range then it will be synthesized using the assembler temporary.

GetATReg() is a callback that can be used to obtain the current assembler temporary and is only called when the assembler temporary is required. It must handle the case where no assembler temporary is available (typically by reporting an error).
